<bioghist altrender="biography" encodinganalog="545" id="a2">
	<head>Historical Note</head>
	<p>The Lowrey Family Reunion Association was comprised of descendants of Thomas and Mary Lowrey, who settled on Red Stone Hill in Plainville, Conn. Reunions of the Lowrey family started being held in 1875.</p>
</bioghist>
<scopecontent encodinganalog="520" id="a3">
	<head>Scope and Content</head>
	<p>Four volumes of record books of genealogical notes regarding the Lowrey family. Record book no. 1 also contains clippings related to the Lowery family reunions.</p>
</scopecontent>
<relatedmaterial encodinganalog="544 1" id="a6">
	<head>Related Material</head>
	<p>The Lowrey family genealogy : addenda to the one hundredth reunion genealogy <extptr linktype="simple" href="http://www.consuls.org/search/o?SEARCH=20225708" show="replace" actuate="onrequest" title="[CSL call number StLib Stacks CS71.L92 1981 Suppl]"/></p>
	<p>Fiftieth anniversary of the descendants of Thomas Lowrey and Mary Lowrey held at Plainville, Connecticut, Wednesday, Aug. 18, 1926 <extptr linktype="simple" href="http://www.consuls.org/search/o?SEARCH=39356433" show="replace" actuate="onrequest" title="[CSL call number StLib Stacks CS71.L92 1926]"/></p>
</relatedmaterial>

